      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cream, bring together, chill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the first 175 g of {{unsalted-butter}} with the {{caster-sugar}} until pale and creamed. Beat in the {{vanilla-extract}}. Sift in the {{plain-flour}}, first 25 g of {{cornflour}} and {{sea-salt-fine}} and bring together by hand to a soft dough. Press between two sheets of baking paper and chill flat for an hour. The cornflour gives a softer, more melt-in-the-mouth biscuit than plain flour alone.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll, cut, bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 170°C fan. Roll the chilled dough between the paper sheets to about 5 mm thick. Cut 32 biscuits with a 5 cm rectangular or oval cutter, pressing straight down. Set on lined trays with 2 cm between each. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes; the biscuits should be pale gold all over with set edges. Cool on the trays for 5 minutes, then on a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Filling, sandwich",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the second 100 g of {{unsalted-butter}} with the {{icing-sugar}}, second 30 g of {{cornflour}} and {{vanilla-bean-paste}} until pale and smooth. Pipe or spread onto the flat side of half the cooled biscuits; sandwich with the remaining biscuits. The filling firms up over the first hour at room temperature.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
